WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:01.704
I'm Steve Castile.

00:01.724 --> 00:07.531
I'm the pastor emeritus here, the seasoned pastor emeritus.

00:08.753 --> 00:12.557
You know, Kelly kind of looked at me when she said that I felt those eyes.

00:14.440 --> 00:18.705
Today, we are continuing our series on salt and light.

00:19.106 --> 00:27.416
And we're talking about the elements that truly make us the church that make us the body of Christ in this world.

00:28.257 --> 00:28.978
And so,

00:29.122 --> 00:34.871
On this day after Valentine's, I have to share kind of a personal aside.

00:35.312 --> 00:41.181
Some of you who have known us for a while know that this is not for us Valentine's week.

00:41.201 --> 00:42.042
This is heart week.

00:43.324 --> 00:48.111
On the 10th of February in 2006, I had quadruple bypass surgery.

00:48.973 --> 00:57.586
I came home on Valentine's Day, which was nice, but Cindy was in the other end of the house with the flu.

00:57.890 --> 01:00.113
And so it was an interesting week.

01:00.133 --> 01:03.737
But today is a critical day in my life.

01:04.678 --> 01:09.504
On the day after Valentine's in Toronto, I met Cindy.

01:09.945 --> 01:12.167
It was the first time we met.

01:12.347 --> 01:18.895
And so Heart Week is made up of, this will be 20 years of survival since my quadruple bypass.

01:19.536 --> 01:23.000
And then Valentine's Day, and then the day I met my wife.

01:23.040 --> 01:24.062
That's pretty cool.

01:24.082 --> 01:27.666
That's why I wear my Tabesco Heart Time today.

01:28.130 --> 01:33.318
It just kind of reminds me that we're in hard week.

01:33.338 --> 01:35.121
Church, I loved Kelly.

01:35.141 --> 01:41.370
The Holy Spirit is a cool thing when she shared with you this kind of symbol of that.

01:41.390 --> 01:43.714
And we're going to allude to that later.

01:43.814 --> 01:50.705
But as a preacher, you always worry about what people think about church.

01:52.868 --> 01:56.754
You always worry that people have the wrong idea about church.

01:57.890 --> 02:07.645
and in our culture that's very easy because sometimes church becomes more of a social club, a place where you go because people go there.

02:09.228 --> 02:26.194
And in that line I'm reminded of an old preacher's joke that this man kept going to this church and he was a homeless guy and he stank and he had long hair and he was just kind of in the eyes of most normal people pretty repulsive but he wouldn't

02:26.274 --> 02:29.597
go there and the ushers would meet him and say, no, you can't go to church here.

02:29.617 --> 02:31.559
You're just, you know, you're too dirty.

02:31.639 --> 02:32.560
We don't know you.

02:33.061 --> 02:34.682
Just know one.

02:34.782 --> 02:39.927
And he had tried one more time and he was sitting on the steps of the church, just kind of sad and rejected.

02:39.967 --> 02:44.452
And Jesus walked up and Jesus says, Hey man, what's going on?

02:45.773 --> 02:54.802
He said, well, I keep trying to go in this church and they keep telling me that I can't go there because I'm not their kind of people.

02:55.746 --> 03:00.612
Jesus sat down beside him and patted his knee and said, listen, man, don't be upset.

03:00.633 --> 03:09.765
I've been trying to get in this church for decades, which brings me back to the whole idea of so, so what is church?

03:11.026 --> 03:13.490
What is the kingdom of God?

03:13.670 --> 03:21.520
And the question that when I titled my sermon, the question that came was, well, where does God go to church?

03:24.304 --> 03:25.746
Where does God go to church?

03:26.914 --> 03:33.884
So many times when we say that word, we think about a building and you think about, you know, putting your hands together and doing that.

03:33.924 --> 03:34.925
Let's, let's do it again.

03:34.945 --> 03:40.433
Uh, we're going to rehearse it at fingers interlaced with the fingers on the inside.

03:41.194 --> 03:42.475
So here's the church.

03:43.276 --> 03:44.398
Here's the steeple.

03:45.900 --> 03:50.166
Open it up and here's the people.

03:50.186 --> 03:53.170
Well, I'm going to tell you a second verse to that.

03:53.666 --> 03:55.147
which I made up myself.

03:57.230 --> 04:01.614
You're going to redo it, put your hands just like this, and you go like this.

04:01.974 --> 04:02.915
Here's the church.

04:04.677 --> 04:06.939
It is the people.

04:06.959 --> 04:09.622
Every once in a while they meet under the steeple.

04:11.964 --> 04:12.625
Try that again.

04:12.685 --> 04:16.429
Here's the church.

04:16.449 --> 04:18.310
It is the people.

04:18.330 --> 04:21.874
Every once in a while they meet under the steeple.

04:23.234 --> 04:28.241
how we look at church really determines how we live out our faith.

04:28.923 --> 04:35.953
One of the joys I get in life is I used to be on TV with the Methodist Tower.

04:35.973 --> 04:40.700
And after COVID, there were so many people preaching, I was like, nobody needs another sermon.

04:40.720 --> 04:43.705
So we started a podcast called The Difference.

04:43.725 --> 04:50.415
And it's a storytelling piece about people in arts and social services that are different than the world.

04:51.076 --> 04:52.658
And they bring

04:52.898 --> 04:58.145
change just because of their work or their art or their life.

04:58.786 --> 05:05.376
And one of the people that I got to do a podcast with was Walter Anderson's son.

05:05.396 --> 05:06.698
Do you all know Walter Anderson?

05:06.878 --> 05:09.141
Great artist from the coast.

05:09.161 --> 05:17.773
His son John has become a friend of ours and Anthony Thakston, who's the producer of our podcast.

05:17.793 --> 05:21.138
And so we ask him if he do a podcast with us and talk about

05:21.634 --> 05:43.826
his dad if you know the story Walter Anderson he was different and a lot of people thought he was crazy but a lot of people didn't know and one of the things Anthony did a documentary on Walter and John discovered some things he didn't know about his dad and so he went on a journey to learn more about his father that maybe he wasn't exactly the man he thought

05:43.938 --> 05:56.957
And in the midst of him excavating some of his writings and revisiting some of the things he said, he said, I came back across a saying that he had shared with me when we were in a conversation.

05:58.039 --> 06:07.352
And it was a conversation about why he was different and why he saw things differently and why he kind of articulated that in a different way.

06:07.412 --> 06:11.218
And he said, John, here's, here's what happens.

06:12.450 --> 06:15.574
People have a perspective, just like an artist does.

06:17.437 --> 06:19.780
And he said, there's really kind of two perspectives.

06:19.840 --> 06:35.802
Those of you that don't know about Walter Anderson need to know that much of his life he spent out on Horn Island, living in nature, canoeing back and forth, boating back and forth, but mostly on the island.

06:35.822 --> 06:41.330
And he said, most people look at the world through

06:41.474 --> 06:46.361
a sure dominant perspective.

06:46.381 --> 06:50.787
I look at the world from an island dominant perspective.

06:53.971 --> 07:07.570
Church invites us not to look at the world in a world dominant perspective, but to look at the world in a kingdom dominant perspective.

07:09.032 --> 07:10.354
It makes us different.

07:11.778 --> 07:15.523
It reshapes how we see things, how we think about things.

07:15.823 --> 07:18.386
When we pray the Lord's prayer, what do we pray?

07:18.446 --> 07:21.810
Thy kingdom come.

07:22.972 --> 07:24.914
Thy will be done.

07:26.957 --> 07:37.970
To be the church means to allow God as what's so beautifully shared by one of the kids and to live in us.

07:38.818 --> 07:46.708
church begins, as Jesus said to Peter, on you will I build my church.

07:48.029 --> 08:00.685
The church is a living, breathing, incredible organism that finds its life when we find our life in Christ.

08:02.487 --> 08:08.274
The scripture that we've put as the centerpiece is in Hebrews and it's

08:09.026 --> 08:17.037
kind of the writer's challenge to the people that Paul's beginning to disciple, the church that's beginning to emerge.

08:17.097 --> 08:19.100
So let's listen to these words.

08:19.661 --> 08:32.639
Therefore my friends, since we have confidence to enter the sanctuary by the blood of Jesus, by the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain that is through his flesh.

08:34.121 --> 08:37.426
And since we have a great priest over the house of God,

08:38.530 --> 08:42.796
Let us approach with true heart in full assurance of faith.

08:43.397 --> 08:50.027
With our hearts sprinkled cleanse from an evil conscience and our body washed with a pure water.

08:51.329 --> 08:59.121
Let us hold fast to the confessions of our hope without wavering, for he who has promised is faithful.

09:01.084 --> 09:07.474
And let us consider how to provoke one another to love and good

09:07.714 --> 09:20.867
deeds, not neglecting meeting together, as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another and all the more as you see the day approaching.

09:22.769 --> 09:30.236
The writer of Hebrews begins that passage by talking about the place where the people of God had worshiped the temple.

09:32.018 --> 09:36.082
And in the temple there were circles, circles of access,

09:38.594 --> 09:46.261
You could stand in the court of the Gentiles if you were not a part of the Jewish faith, but you couldn't go beyond that.

09:47.563 --> 09:53.949
And then there was another circle where those who were a part of the Jewish faith could go and worship.

09:54.249 --> 09:56.972
And then there was the priest who would lead the worship.

09:57.392 --> 10:00.415
And then behind the priest, there was this huge curtain.

10:02.097 --> 10:07.602
And behind the curtain was where God was supposed to live in that holy temple.

10:08.098 --> 10:22.160
and no one but the priest could ever go through that curtain except for once a year where they went and made an offering of sin atonement to God.

10:23.301 --> 10:34.098
And there would always be a holding of your breath because nobody knew if the priest would come back out because to be in the presence of God was something that was overwhelming.

10:35.778 --> 10:46.869
But if you remember the story of the crucifixion of Jesus, as Jesus died, there was an earthquake.

10:48.851 --> 10:55.517
And in that temple, that huge curtain was torn down.

10:59.961 --> 11:04.946
And in that incredible miraculous act, God made a statement to us.

11:06.690 --> 11:08.252
The church is not a place.

11:10.074 --> 11:12.376
God's presence cannot be curated.

11:14.138 --> 11:20.085
God's greatest desire is the same desire that he had when he created us.

11:21.566 --> 11:29.415
That is to walk with us and talk with us and live with us and live in us.

11:31.077 --> 11:35.922
To create a sacred community that was his blessed creation.

11:36.546 --> 11:56.082
And in Jesus, He came to send us the message that not even death is going to keep Him from building His church, from being in community with us, from inviting us to be in community with Him.

11:59.010 --> 12:02.273
And so what church truly is is not a facility.

12:02.593 --> 12:03.875
Facilities are incredible.

12:03.915 --> 12:08.980
This is a place where supposedly we hope the work of the kingdom takes place.

12:11.002 --> 12:17.248
It is bricks and mortar, but it is not God's house.

12:23.634 --> 12:27.698
It is the place where we gather and invite God to come join us.

12:28.450 --> 12:36.642
It is a place where we come together to remember the covenant we have made together as the body of Christ to live in the world as Jesus did.

12:38.385 --> 12:48.399
We keep this building to serve, to glorify, to gather, but it is not the church we are.

12:51.103 --> 12:55.309
So what does the church look like?

12:55.329 --> 12:55.730
Well,

12:56.930 --> 12:59.253
How many of you have joined this church?

13:00.295 --> 13:04.301
That's not that I'm trying to smoke you out or anything, but let me just, how many of you joined?

13:04.321 --> 13:09.248
Do you remember when you joined, did you make some vows?

13:12.813 --> 13:16.378
You see, the truth is what the church is, is a covenantal relationship.

13:16.699 --> 13:24.530
I went to the Board of Discipleships website and you can print out your membership vows in gold, in silver,

13:24.802 --> 13:27.865
I print them out in red today for Valentine's Day.

13:27.885 --> 13:32.570
I want you to listen to the covenant you make when you become a part of our church.

13:36.854 --> 13:43.841
To renounce the spiritual forces of wickedness and reject the evil of this world and repent of our sins.

13:45.262 --> 13:47.485
Thy kingdom come.

13:47.505 --> 13:49.607
To accept the freedom and power of God.

13:49.627 --> 13:52.850
To resist evil injustice and oppression.

13:54.594 --> 14:22.834
to live like Christ lived, to confess Jesus Christ as Savior and put our whole trust in His grace and to serve Him as our Lord, to be about the work of God, to remain faithful members of Christ's Holy Church and to serve as Christ's representative in the world, to be loyal to Christ,

14:23.906 --> 14:26.950
and to do all in our power to strengthen the ministry.

14:28.832 --> 14:40.448
To be faithful, this is the part that most people remember, to be faithful participants in its ministries by what our prayers, our presence, our gifts, our service, and our witness.

14:41.589 --> 14:51.282
And then finally, to receive and profess the Christian faith as contained in the scriptures of both the old and new testament.

14:52.578 --> 14:53.840
Do you see what that is?

14:53.860 --> 14:58.288
It is a framework for a culture and a way of life.

14:59.410 --> 15:02.015
This is heaven culture, not world culture.

15:02.977 --> 15:05.982
This is Jesus' way, not the world's way.

15:06.443 --> 15:12.754
And to be a part of the church is to make a covenant relationship that says, God, I have decided,

15:13.026 --> 15:22.721
to be your child, as you created me to be, to walk with you, to talk with you, to live for you, to serve you, just like Jesus did.

15:24.103 --> 15:41.330
And in doing that, I invite you into my life fully to bring direction, but not only direction to my life, to bring me together in a countable community that we can create outposts of heaven all over this world.

15:44.098 --> 15:53.753
that people can look at this building when we gather in it and say, I think God goes to church there.

15:56.256 --> 15:58.680
I think God's spirit is present there.

16:01.184 --> 16:13.042
In my ministry, I've had a chance to be in places that were sacred places, places where I know God's Holy Spirit was and where the church was truly, indeed, present.

16:14.562 --> 16:21.596
Whenever I left here and went to the conference office, one of the things that we began to emphasize was homeless ministry.

16:21.616 --> 16:24.021
There at the Capitol, there were so many homeless people.

16:24.101 --> 16:27.808
And so at annual conference, I decided to bring somebody in to speak about it.

16:28.750 --> 16:32.798
He lived in Philadelphia, part of a ministry called Mission Year.

16:34.201 --> 16:36.946
And so I decided to go vet that.

16:37.698 --> 16:45.430
So I went to Philadelphia and got there thinking I was just going to speak to Chris Larr, who was the person who was coming, who was a part of Mission Year.

16:47.333 --> 16:51.839
And Chris said, oh, you just, you know, I forgot to tell you, I've got a little plan for you.

16:53.282 --> 16:54.604
I was like, yeah, what's that plan?

16:54.984 --> 17:00.973
He said, you know, we've got a crew in that's a new crew that's coming to spend a year in Mission here in Philadelphia with the homeless people.

17:01.434 --> 17:06.802
And their initiation is what we call the pulpers ride a passage, which means

17:07.106 --> 17:09.489
In the morning, you're going to get up after tonight.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.333
We go to a thrift shop and you pick five pieces of clothes.

17:12.733 --> 17:16.037
And we're going to take you into Philadelphia and drop you in Love Park.

17:16.077 --> 17:19.702
And you're going to be there as a homeless person for the next 12 hours.

17:20.222 --> 17:21.985
And we're going to give you a little checklist.

17:22.005 --> 17:23.487
You're going to have to dumpster dive.

17:23.507 --> 17:25.429
You're going to have to go to homeless shelters.

17:25.850 --> 17:29.534
You're going to have to not stay inside more than 15 minutes.

17:29.594 --> 17:34.100
And I'm like, you know, Chris, I just came to talk to you about coming to annual conference.

17:34.120 --> 17:35.762
He said, nah, you got this.

17:36.802 --> 17:37.283
So I did.

17:37.323 --> 17:40.266
We went that night and we went to the thrift shop.

17:40.966 --> 17:44.230
I picked out five pieces of clothes and that had to include your underwear.

17:44.310 --> 17:48.034
And so I got some jeans, got my underwear, got some socks.

17:48.054 --> 17:49.455
That's three pieces right there.

17:50.236 --> 17:52.519
And so I thought, well, you know, I'm probably going to need a hat.

17:52.559 --> 17:56.363
So I got a toboggan because it was October in Philadelphia.

17:58.205 --> 18:03.090
And then I was like, hmm, and I just saw this cool t-shirt.

18:04.962 --> 18:12.029
And I was drawn to it, so I got the t-shirt, not thinking that it was 42 degrees outside, and then I was gonna be outside the rest of the day.

18:12.749 --> 18:18.395
So that next morning, they gave us our peanut butter and jelly sandwich in the church, and they gave us a token.

18:18.475 --> 18:22.318
We took the subway into Love Park, and the first thing we had to do was beg.

18:25.261 --> 18:27.383
It was 45 minutes of humiliation.

18:28.484 --> 18:34.770
As we went down the checklist, and as we were making our way, we went to one of the parks where the veterans was, and this guy

18:35.010 --> 18:38.656
We walked upon these two veterans that were on a bench, Quinn and Tony.

18:39.718 --> 18:42.562
And as soon as we walked up, they looked at us and said, y'all are not homeless.

18:42.683 --> 18:44.626
What are y'all doing here?

18:45.587 --> 18:52.459
We explained it to them, and Quinn, who was kind of the instigator, said, oh, I can't let y'all wander around Philadelphia by yourselves.

18:52.859 --> 18:53.981
We're going to protect you.

18:54.061 --> 18:59.390
So come on, I'll give you a tour of Philly, and we'll take you to all the best places for homeless people to eat.

18:59.871 --> 19:00.752
Who knew, you know?

19:01.273 --> 19:01.874
It's like,

19:02.018 --> 19:06.702
And so they said, well, the Korean truck over by the river, they have the best hot food and so forth.

19:06.722 --> 19:08.424
But you don't have a coat, man.

19:08.464 --> 19:09.305
None of y'all have a coat.

19:09.565 --> 19:16.011
We're going to go to the church of the Red Door, which got my curiosity up.

19:16.031 --> 19:28.083
But he let us through, took us first through the mall, which by the way, if you're ever homeless and it was raining and you're wet, if you go into the outer lobby of a mall, there is the return air for their conditioner system.

19:28.123 --> 19:31.346
You can stand over that and it will dry you out in about five minutes.

19:34.018 --> 19:36.702
After we had finished there, he took us to the church of the Red Door.

19:37.062 --> 19:39.065
And sure enough, there was the Red Door.

19:39.145 --> 19:40.828
That's really all I remember about it.

19:40.888 --> 19:46.195
What I remember most is when we walked in, there was a woman that met us and said, oh, babies, y'all, come in.

19:46.255 --> 19:47.397
Y'all must be freezing.

19:47.417 --> 19:48.559
We got to get you some coats.

19:48.639 --> 19:50.541
Go sit over there and get you some snacks.

19:51.102 --> 19:59.474
And as we looked around the room, they were indeed a safe place for lots of homeless people and nestled throughout the room were volunteers and

19:59.586 --> 20:07.519
church staff who were talking to the people that were there who were encouraging them, who were kind of counseling with them.

20:08.681 --> 20:13.609
And so this lady disappeared and went down into the basement of the church and came out.

20:13.930 --> 20:14.931
There were four of us.

20:14.992 --> 20:16.654
They didn't send us out by ourselves.

20:17.035 --> 20:19.739
And so they, she came back with three coats.

20:21.322 --> 20:24.708
And she gave the two young women that were with us, their coats and the other young man.

20:24.768 --> 20:26.130
And she looked at me and she said,

20:26.370 --> 20:26.670
Mr.

20:26.710 --> 20:28.753
I couldn't find a coat in our coat cloth.

20:28.873 --> 20:31.016
And then she said, well, this is not right.

20:31.116 --> 20:31.657
Come with me.

20:32.958 --> 20:38.846
And so she took me down two steps of two flights of steps all the way down into the basement below the basement.

20:38.866 --> 20:42.871
It was dark and she goes into this closet and she just starts praying out loud.

20:42.931 --> 20:44.874
Dear Jesus, we need a coat.

20:44.894 --> 20:48.418
Dear Jesus, please let there be a coat in this place that fits this man.

20:48.839 --> 20:50.882
Dear Jen, she walked down and said, thank you, Lord.

20:51.382 --> 20:54.386
And she had this beautiful herringbone peak coat.

20:55.778 --> 20:58.282
And she said, God is good.

21:01.226 --> 21:05.392
I took the coat, went back up, our 15 minutes was up, and so we went back on the street.

21:06.434 --> 21:13.605
The long and the short of it was I felt more at church there than I've just about ever felt in my life.

21:13.685 --> 21:13.985
Why?

21:14.005 --> 21:25.042
Not because of an incredible praise team, which we have, not because of a beautiful facility, but because regardless of who I was, I was loved.

21:27.266 --> 21:29.488
We got time for the bus to pick us up.

21:29.568 --> 21:33.753
Quinn and Tony were sitting there waiting with us because they knew what we'd been doing.

21:34.754 --> 21:48.468
And Tony, who was a disabled vet, lifted up his backpack, which I'd been helping him carry and unzipped it and said, look, we can't have you come to the city of brotherly love and leave empty handed.

21:50.370 --> 21:54.354
And he pulled out of the bag a brand new Eagles playoff t-shirt.

21:55.650 --> 21:59.614
And he said, next time you come, bring more clothes.

21:59.634 --> 22:00.936
And he handed me the t-shirt.

22:02.217 --> 22:03.739
I have it along with that toboggan.

22:03.799 --> 22:08.905
And every once in a while, I just wear it to remind me of what church feels like.

22:10.006 --> 22:12.168
You see, church is not a building.

22:12.228 --> 22:16.213
It's not a set of beliefs, even though we have them.

22:17.834 --> 22:21.138
It is a covenantal relationship with the God who made us.

22:23.042 --> 22:33.394
And the beautiful miracle of it is as we live into that, God weaves us together into a community of faith that loves and cares and reaches out for each other.

22:36.858 --> 22:38.359
There are a lot of ways to look at it.

22:39.340 --> 22:41.763
One of my favorite writers is Erwin McManus.

22:42.884 --> 22:47.890
He's made, so he's seasoned, but he's written a bunch of books.

22:49.058 --> 22:54.104
And one of my favorite books he wrote is called The Barbarian Way, The Barbarian Way.

22:54.625 --> 23:00.411
And he talks about the fact that being a Christian automatically puts us counterculture to the world we live in.

23:00.672 --> 23:03.495
And people don't understand why we do things the way we do.

23:03.535 --> 23:08.521
And he was going to do a speech on that with his daughter, who is just brilliant.

23:09.182 --> 23:12.786
And he said, maybe I'm trying to figure out a new way

23:12.898 --> 23:16.021
of saying how we as Christians live different than the world.

23:16.102 --> 23:18.164
And she said, dad, you've been doing this a long time.

23:18.204 --> 23:19.405
This should really be easy.

23:21.167 --> 23:23.430
She said, I put it in two sentences.

23:25.352 --> 23:31.278
Jesus teaches us to love to live and to live to love.

23:36.784 --> 23:39.888
It sounds kind of like Jesus is three, two commandments.

23:40.168 --> 23:42.130
Love God, love neighbor, love self.

23:42.978 --> 23:45.482
The church is people who live to love.

23:45.502 --> 23:52.151
And the reason that I put this in here is because so many people think that when you become a member of a church, you give up all fun.

23:53.393 --> 23:54.435
You ever read the gospels?

23:55.076 --> 23:57.019
How many times do we find Jesus at a party?

23:59.082 --> 24:07.634
How many times do we find Jesus talking about a banquet and a celebration and the kingdom of God is like a party?

24:09.986 --> 24:14.211
to be a part of the church is learned to live into the life that Jesus promised.

24:14.612 --> 24:19.999
I promise that I came to give you life and give it more abundantly.

24:22.442 --> 24:27.288
And so God gives us a gift of life, but then He gives us the wonder of the gift of love.

24:27.588 --> 24:33.395
The church should be the most loving community in creation.

24:36.980 --> 24:38.642
And that love is born.

24:38.978 --> 24:42.843
out of God's love for us and what is done inside of us.

24:44.745 --> 24:51.114
In second chapter of Acts, we have this beautiful snapshot of what the church looks like whenever it's there.

24:51.434 --> 24:58.483
It's after Peter is preached, there's thousands of people who've been baptized, they're learning how to be the kingdom on earth together.

24:58.543 --> 25:03.890
And in that second chapter, beginning in the 42nd verse, we see these words.

25:07.106 --> 25:14.133
And they devoted themselves to the apostles' teaching and fellowship, to the breaking of bread and the prayers.

25:16.094 --> 25:21.900
All came upon everyone because many signs, wonders and signs were being done by the apostles.

25:23.241 --> 25:28.126
All who believed were together and had all things in common.

25:28.346 --> 25:29.868
Doesn't sound like the world right now.

25:30.929 --> 25:36.754
They would sell their possessions and goods and distribute the proceeds to all as any had need.

25:38.082 --> 25:50.794
Day by day, as they spent much time together in the temple, they broke bread at home, ate their food with glad and generous hearts, praising God and having the goodwill of all the people.

25:51.715 --> 25:58.682
And day by day, the Lord added to their number those who were being saved.

26:00.284 --> 26:01.805
That is church.

26:06.029 --> 26:06.930
Eating together.

26:08.034 --> 26:28.225
sharing together, loving each other, and being such a present salt and light in the world that people who see us want to be us, want to be a part, want to learn to live like that.

26:31.410 --> 26:34.354
And when we begin to live like that,

26:36.866 --> 26:40.250
then God wants to go to church there.

26:43.114 --> 26:47.240
Because that's the snapshot of how we live.

26:49.402 --> 26:56.291
And I want to close with the snapshot of how God wants to see the world.

26:56.992 --> 26:58.154
You've heard it many of you.

26:58.174 --> 27:00.337
It's in Revelation 21 chapter.

27:01.198 --> 27:04.402
This is God's picture of church.

27:05.570 --> 27:12.219
Then we saw a new heaven and a new earth and the first heaven and the first earth had passed away and the sea was no more.

27:13.420 --> 27:21.271
And I saw a holy city, a new Jerusalem coming down out of heaven that God has prepared as a bride adorned for her husband.

27:22.493 --> 27:28.921
And I heard a loud voice from the throne saying, see, the home of God is among mortals.

27:29.302 --> 27:35.570
He will dwell with them and they will be his people and God himself will be with them.

27:36.674 --> 27:38.796
and he'll wipe away every tear from their eyes.

27:38.836 --> 27:40.798
This will be no more.

27:40.878 --> 27:46.543
Morning and crying and pain will be no more, for the first things have passed away.

27:46.583 --> 27:54.471
And the one who was seated on the throne said, see, I'm making all things new.

27:54.511 --> 28:02.358
He also said, write this for these words are trustworthy and true.

28:04.841 --> 28:06.322
The God who made us

28:07.202 --> 28:09.685
wants to live in us and among us.

28:10.686 --> 28:33.951
And every time we let that happen in our life, and every time we begin to live together as it happens, as we answer our calls, as we live into our talents, as we seek to serve God in the places He calls us to, then we become more and more like that kingdom that is to come.

28:35.473 --> 28:36.594
In this day,

28:41.538 --> 28:44.441
The world needs us so much.

28:47.444 --> 28:58.295
In this day, people are looking for a place to live and be loved.

29:00.378 --> 29:03.060
In this day, we're called to be that.

29:05.383 --> 29:08.466
And if you've made the covenant to be a part of this church,

29:11.106 --> 29:28.690
then I invite you to recommit to that covenant, that when it comes time for us to worship, we can say, hey, God goes to church here.

29:31.313 --> 29:31.794
Let us pray.

